<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        WINDSHIELD WIPERS (AIR) - CONTROL VALVES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CONTROL VALVES</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The control valves for both wipers are mounted in the base of the instrument console. To remove either
                valve:
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift access cover from top of instrument console.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four screws and detach rectangular panel from the instrument console.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a small hex key wrench, loosen the set screws and detach knobs from the control
                    valves.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove jam nuts and detach control valves from the rectangular panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600677">Figure 77</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1600677" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1600677" filename="../figg16/G1600677.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 77. Removing Control Valves</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect air lines from the valves. The control valves are serviced as an assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600678">Figure 78</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1600678" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1600678" filename="../figg16/G1600678.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 78. Control Valve Assembly</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. VALVE ASSEMBLY, WIPER CONTROL</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. SET SCREW</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. KNOB, CONTROL VALVE</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. HEX NUT</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. LOCKWASHER</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. CONTROL VALVE</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect air lines to the valves.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach control valves to the rectangular panel with jam nuts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach knobs to the control valves and secure with set screws. Tighten with a small hex
                    key wrench.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach rectangular panel with valves installed to the instrument console.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure access cover to top of instrument console.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
